<br />
<br />
<span style="color:#3498db;"><strong>1. Visa Support</strong></span><br />
<br />
In the survey, it was the part that was most needed.<br />
<br />
Currently, we will only provide services related to D10 visa, but we plan to broaden the scope.<br />
<br />
The lawyer of BKL, the second biggest law firm in Korea, is going to help.<br />
<br />
The profile of the attorney is as follows.<br />
<br />
http://bitly.kr/HirediversityVisa<br />
<br />
<br />
<span style="color:#3498db;"><strong>2. Reputation Report</strong></span><br />
<br />
Our survey shows that the biggest reason for the difficulties involved in finding a job in Korea is that foreigners do not know about the company<br />
<br />
So we&#39;ll investigate important things in the decision to get a job.<br />
<br />
For example,<br />
(1) The average salary for the job<br />
<br />
(2) Size of company<br />
<br />
(3) The thoughts that company employees have about the company<br />
<br />
We think the above information will also help with salary negotiation.<br />
<br />
<br />
<span style="color:#3498db;"><strong>3. Point system</strong></span><br />
<br />
Hirediversity has been created a point system to better communicate with our friend.<br />
<br />
How to get point:<br />
<br />
1. Get 10 points for every new login every day.<br />
2. If you recommend joining a friend, friends and referrers get 100 points.<br />
3. You will receive 100 points when you sign up.<br />
4. Get 10 points when participating in surveys coming up on an irregular basis<br />
(Will be posted on the first page)<br />
<br />
<br />
The points you collect during the Beta service period will be available to use the services provided<br />
by Hirediversity even after the Beta service.<br />
(All points issued during testing before service start have been initialized)<br />
<br />
<span style="color:#27ae60;">How to use the point &lt;2019.02. 26.&gt;<br />
<br />
--- preparing ---<br />
<br />
(If there are too many users on a particular service and need priority, we will require points<br />
Ex : &quot;E7 visa documentation&quot;, &quot;offline job fair&quot; )</span><br />
<br />
<important notice=""></important></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><important notice=""><br />
